@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### 1) LOGIN (gera access_token e registra auditoria LOGIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "admin",
  "senha": "admin123"
}

### Copie o token retornado acima
@token = COLE_O_ACCESS_TOKEN_AQUI

### 2) CREATE Cliente (registra auditoria CREATE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/clientes/
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nome": "Cliente Auditoria",
  "cpf": "98765432100",
  "telefone": "11911111111"
}

### 3) UPDATE Cliente (registra dados_antigos + dados_novos)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/clientes/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "nome": "Cliente Auditoria Atualizado",
  "telefone": "11922222222"
}

### 4) DELETE Cliente (registra dados_antigos)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/clientes/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5) Consultar auditoria (apenas grupo admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auditoria/?limit=100
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6) Health full (DB + tabelas + sistema)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health/full

### 6.1) Readiness
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

### 6.2) Liveness
GET {{baseUrl}}/live

### 7) Rate limiting (dispare repetidamente para receber 429)
# Execute este bloco varias vezes em menos de 1 minuto.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
